---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const seo = {
  title: "CPP and OAS Benefits in Canada (2026 Guide)",
  description: "Comprehensive guide to Canada Pension Plan (CPP) and Old Age Security (OAS) benefits, contribution rules, early/late claiming factors, and OAS clawback thresholds.",
  schema: `
    <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
      {
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "Article",
        "headline": "CPP and OAS Benefits in Canada",
        "author": {
          "@type": "Person",
          "name": "Mrittunjoy Das"
        },
        "publisher": {
          "@type": "Organization",
          "name": "TaxDebtWealthSuite"
        },
        "datePublished": "2026-07-23",
        "dateModified": "2026-07-23",
        "description": "Comprehensive guide to Canada Pension Plan (CPP) and Old Age Security (OAS) benefits, contribution rules, and OAS clawback thresholds."
      }
    </script>
    <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
      {
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How does early CPP retirement affect my payment?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Taking CPP at age 60 reduces your monthly payment by 36% (-0.6% per month before age 65). Delaying to age 70 increases your CPP payment by 42% (+0.7% per month)."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the OAS Clawback threshold in Canada?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "For 2026, the OAS recovery tax threshold starts at net individual income above C$90,997. OAS is reduced by 15 cents for every dollar of income above this limit."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    </script>
  `
};
---

<Layout title={seo.title} description={seo.description} head={seo.schema}>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <header class="mb-12 text-center">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-400 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest border border-emerald-500/20 mb-6">
        <span>Canada Pension & OAS</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-white tracking-tight mb-6 leading-tight">
        CPP and OAS Benefits in Canada
      </h1>
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4 text-sm text-slate-400">
        <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <img src="https://ui-avatars.com/api/?name=Mrittunjoy+Das&background=00F5D4&color=000" alt="Mrittunjoy Das" class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full" />
          By <span class="text-white font-medium">Mrittunjoy Das</span>
        </span>
        <span>•</span>
        <time datetime="2026-07-23">July 23, 2026</time>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Embedded Calculator Callout Banner -->
    <div class="my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-r from-[#141C32] to-[#1E294B] border border-[#00F5D4]/30 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
      <div class="space-y-1">
        <span class="text-xs font-bold text-[#00F5D4] uppercase tracking-wider">Interactive Tool</span>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">Canada CPP & OAS Pension Estimator</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate-300">Calculate your estimated combined CPP and OAS monthly payouts.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/social-security-pension-estimator/canada/" class="px-5 py-2.5 rounded-xl bg-[#00F5D4] hover:bg-[#00F5D4]/90 text-slate-950 font-bold text-xs whitespace-nowrap transition-all shadow-lg shadow-[#00F5D4]/20">
        Estimate CPP & OAS →
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8 text-slate-300 text-base leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Public retirement income in Canada is built on two primary pillars administered by Service Canada: the <strong>Canada Pension Plan (CPP)</strong> and <strong>Old Age Security (OAS)</strong>. Together, CPP and OAS provide a predictable income baseline for Canadian retirees.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white border-b border-slate-800 pb-3">1. Understanding the Canada Pension Plan (CPP)</h2>
      <p>
        CPP is an earnings-related benefit replacing approximately 25% to 33% of your average pre-retirement employment earnings. Maximum CPP at age 65 is <strong>C$1,364.60 per month</strong>. Claiming early at age 60 reduces your payout by 36%, while delaying until age 70 boosts your payout by 42%.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white border-b border-slate-800 pb-3">2. Understanding Old Age Security (OAS)</h2>
      <p>
        OAS is a residency-based benefit providing up to <strong>C$713.34 per month</strong> at age 65 for individuals with 40 years of Canadian residence after age 18. OAS increases by 10% automatically at age 75.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white border-b border-slate-800 pb-3">3. OAS Recovery Tax (Clawback)</h2>
      <p>
        For 2026, the OAS clawback threshold begins at net individual income exceeding <strong>C$90,997</strong>, reducing OAS by 15 cents for every dollar over the threshold.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white border-b border-slate-800 pb-3">Related Calculators & Strategy Guides</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
        <a href="/social-security-pension-estimator/canada/" class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 hover:border-[#00F5D4]/40 transition-all space-y-2">
          <span class="text-xs font-bold text-[#00F5D4] uppercase">Calculator</span>
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-white">CPP & OAS Estimator</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">Calculate your Canadian CPP and OAS monthly payouts.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/rmd-calculator/canada/" class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 hover:border-indigo-500/40 transition-all space-y-2">
          <span class="text-xs font-bold text-indigo-400 uppercase">Related Tool</span>
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-white">RRIF Minimum Calculator</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">Model mandatory CRA minimum withdrawals for RRIFs.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/roth-conversion-calculator/" class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 hover:border-amber-500/40 transition-all space-y-2">
          <span class="text-xs font-bold text-amber-400 uppercase">Related Tool</span>
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-white">Roth & Tax Conversion Tool</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">Explore tax-bracket management strategies.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
